## вҡҷпёҸ How It Works

### 1. Data Collection
Representatives submit failure reports through a **Slack application (MELI FO)** with a structured form capturing: LDAP, Team Leader, failure type, details, and date.

### 2. Data Storage
Slack automatically inserts records into a centralized **Google Sheets** database.

### 3. Automated Processing (n8n)
Three separate workflows process and deliver reports:

| Workflow | Schedule | Content |
|----------|----------|---------|
| **Daily** | Every morning | Previous day's failures per TL, occurrence list |
| **Weekly** | Every Monday | Week summary, Top 3 reps, % variation vs previous week |
| **Monthly** | 1st of each month | Full month overview, distribution by type, rep ranking |

### 4. Auto-fill Temporal Fields
A separate n8n workflow runs every 10 minutes, automatically calculating and filling **Month, Week, and Year** for new records.

### 5. Visualization
**Looker Studio** dashboards provide real-time visibility with KPIs for failure rates, trends, and team performance.

